description:
➤ Foundations of Faith Archives:
https://www.amazingfacts.org/media-library/watch/archives/o/1205/t/foundations-of-faith

If we're going to understand salvation, we must understand something about sin and how it is defined - the laws of life and love.

chapters.title: <Untitled Chapter 1>
Presentation 2 THE LAWS OF LIFE AND LOVE
Whom does the devil especially hate?
Can God's moral law be changed or repealed?
According to the Bible, what is sin?
To what law does 1 John 3:4 refer?
Did Jesus keep the Ten Commandments?
How many have sinned and what is the penalty?
Some say the Ten Commandments are not binding for New Testament Christians. What does Jesus say about this? FOUNDATIONS OF FAITH
If thou wilt enter into life, keep the commandments.
If ye love me, keep my commandments. John 14:15
Here is the patience of the saints: here are they that keep the commandments of God.
Billy Graham: "My Answer"
Are people saved by keeping the law?
Doesn't living under grace, by faith, make keeping God's law non-essential?
How is it possible to keep the commandments?
I can do all things through Christ which strengtheneth me. Philippians 4:13
What is the old covenant, and why did it fail?
Are some Old Testament laws no longer binding upon Christians?
Therefore love is the fulfilling of the law. Romans 13:10
Can I be a true Christian without keeping His commandments?
What are some of the glorious rewards of keeping God's law?
Oh, that you had heeded My commandments! Then your peace would have been like a river, and your righteousness like the waves of the sea. Isaiah 48:18
